==English==
===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|IHVH}}, {{l|en|IHWH}}, {{l|en|JHVH}}, {{l|en|JHWH}}, {{l|en|YHVH}}
===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# Known as the "[[Tetragrammaton]]", the four Hebrew letters {{l|he|יהוה}} which are transliterated into the Latin alphabet as YHWH (or IHVH, JHVH, or [[YHVH]]). Usually vowels are added to produce the spelling [[Jehovah]], [[Yehovah]] or [[Yahweh]] ([[Jahaveh]], [[Jahve]], [[Jahveh]], [[Jahweh]], [[Yahve]], [[Yahveh]], [[Yahwe]]).
